========,3,Transportation.
Transportation in Giza comprises an extensive road network, rail system, subway system, and maritime services.
Road transport is facilitated by personal vehicles, taxi cabs, privately owned public buses and microbuses.
Giza shares with Cairo a subway system, officially called the "Metro (مترو)", a fast and efficient way of getting around.
An extensive road network connects Giza with 6th of October City, Cairo and other cities.
There are flyovers and bridges such as the 15th Giza traffic is known to be overwhelming and overcrowded.
